// Exercises three grammar gaps recently wired (set / as / invoke):
//  - `set` sets a query-level option before the query (querytrace here).
//  - `| as Result` binds a name to the intermediate rowset (a row-wise no-op
//    at emit; the name is metadata for later reference / invoke).
//  - `| invoke MyPlugin()` calls a stored function on the rowset (parsed +
//    translated as a pass-through; real semantics need a function registry).
set querytrace;
SecurityEvent
| where EventID == 4624
| summarize LogonCount = count() by Account
| as AdminLogons
| invoke DetectAnomaly(LogonCount)
| take 10
